import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='region', y='income', data=data, palette='Set2')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Income')
    plt.legend(title='Region', loc='upper right', labels=data['region'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different regions?', wrap=True)

    plt.legend(title='Region', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('region').agg({'income': 'mean', 'health': 'mean'}).reset_index()
    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()
    ax2 = ax1.twinx()

    sns.barplot(x='region', y='income', data=data_grouped, ax=ax1, alpha=0.5, label='Average Income')
    sns.barplot(x='region', y='health', data=data_grouped, ax=ax2, alpha=0.5, label='Average Health')

    ax1.set_ylabel('Average Income')
    ax2.set_ylabel('Average Health')
    ax1.set_xticklabels(ax1.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the average income and health for each region?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
